// INTEGRATION POINTS:
//
// 1. Frontend (Chatbot.astro component):
//    POST /api/v1/chat
//    Request: { message: string, systemPrompt: string }
//    Response: { response: string } or { error: string }
//
// 2. Environment Variables (.env or GitHub Secrets):
//    OPENROUTER_API_KEY=sk-xxx...
//    OPENROUTER_MODEL=openai/gpt-4-turbo (optional, defaults to gpt-4-turbo)
//    OPENROUTER_BASE_URL=https://openrouter.ai/api/v1 (optional)
//
// 3. GitHub Actions (helm-release.yml):
//    Uses OPENROUTER_API_KEY secret during deployment
//    Sets environment variable in deployed pod
//
// 4. Helm Chart (values.yaml):
//    env:
//      OPENROUTER_API_KEY:
//        secretRef:
//          name: pushpaka-secrets
//          key: OPENROUTER_API_KEY

// TESTING:
//
// Test the endpoint locally:
// curl -X POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/chat \
//   -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
//   -d '{
//     "message": "How do I install Pushpaka?",
//     "systemPrompt": "[80+ line system prompt from Chatbot.astro]"
//   }'

// RATE LIMITING CONSIDERATIONS:
//
// Recommended middleware:
// - 10 requests per minute per IP (public endpoint)
// - 100 requests per minute for authenticated users
// - 1000 requests per day per user
// - Burst limit: 5 concurrent requests
//
// Rate Limit Headers:
// X-RateLimit-Limit: 10
// X-RateLimit-Remaining: 9
// X-RateLimit-Reset: 1234567890

// ERROR HANDLING:
//
// Return user-friendly errors:
// - 400: Invalid request (message too long, empty, etc.)
// - 429: Rate limited (too many requests)
// - 500: Internal error (don't expose API key issues)
// - 503: Service unavailable (chatbot not configured)

// SECURITY NOTES:
//
// ✅ API key stored only in environment (never in code/logs)
// ✅ API key never returned to frontend
// ✅ Rate limited to prevent abuse
// ✅ Timeout set to 30s to prevent hanging
// ✅ CORS configured to allow only trusted origins
// ✅ Input validated (max 5000 chars per message)
// ✅ Errors don't expose sensitive information
